The MPEG-1 specification is divided into five parts: Systems, Video, Audio, Compliance testing, and Software simulation. 

* The Systems part (ISO/IEC 11172-1) provides the framework for the overall system but does not specify details about decoding and synchronization. 
* Part 2 (ISO/IEC 11172-2) specifically deals with the compression and encoding of video in MPEG-1. This includes the method for transforming and approximating video signals, which forms the basis for the video encoding in the format. 
* The Audio part (ISO/IEC 11172-3) centers around the compression and encoding of audio. This includes defining details of the audio bitstream, the tools used for analysis and encoding, and other requirements for compressing audio components. 
* Part 4 (ISO/IEC 11172-4) addresses compliance testing, which plays a critical role in ensuring that all equipment and components meet the requirements set out in the ISO/IEC 11172 specification. 
* Finally, Part 5 of MPEG-1 (ISO/IEC TR 11172-5) is focused on software simulation.
